<!-- The Contribution Process -->
<section class="section-mist section-pad">
  <div class="page-container" style="max-width: 64rem;">
    <p class="overline">How knowledge enters</p>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.875rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Contribution Process</h2>
    <p class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">Nothing arrives in the Library directly. Every piece of knowledge travels a defined path: from outside the island, through the Harbour, into Streams where it forms, and only then — if it passes the Enactment Process — into the canonical Library.</p>

    <!-- Flow steps -->
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0;">
      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: start; padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-ocean); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;">
          {{ kiIcon("harbour", 20) }}
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.0625rem; margin-bottom: 0.375rem;">1 — Harbour receives</h3>
          <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">Material arrives from outside — email, notes, conversations, linked references. The Harbour is the port of entry: nothing has been assessed yet, nothing is canonical. It exists so material is not lost before someone can look at it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: start; padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-teal); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;">
          {{ kiIcon("current", 20) }}
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.0625rem; margin-bottom: 0.375rem;">2 — Streams form it</h3>
          <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">From the Harbour, material moves into Streams — the living edge where knowledge is forming but not yet canonical. Notes connect to other notes. Patterns emerge. A Stream is always in motion; it is the island's working memory.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: start; padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-forest); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;">
          {{ kiIcon("lighthouse", 20) }}
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.0625rem; margin-bottom: 0.375rem;">3 — Enactment assesses</h3>
          <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">A council member proposes a change via the Enactment Process — the governance gate. Proposals must be scoped, generic enough to belong in the canonical Library, and ratified by the Council before they alter any Pillar. Visitors can identify gaps; only council members may propose changes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Step 4 -->
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: start; padding: 1.5rem 0;">
        <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-gold); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;">
          {{ kiIcon("book", 20) }}
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.0625rem; margin-bottom: 0.375rem;">4 — Library holds it</h3>
          <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">Ratified knowledge enters the Library — the canonical record. The Calendar holds what happened; the Pillars hold the model; the Resources hold reference material. Once in the Library, knowledge is stable — changes require a new Enactment proposal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Establishing Your Island -->
<section class="section-parchment section-pad">
  <div class="page-container" style="max-width: 64rem;">
    <p class="overline">Starting from scratch</p>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.875rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Establishing Your Island</h2>
    <p class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">Every island requires three things before it can function as a Knowledge Island: a Charter, a Knowledge Capital, and a Contribution Process. These are not optional — they are what distinguishes a Knowledge Island from a folder of notes.</p>

    <div class="grid-3col" style="gap: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="card-ki">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <div class="symbol-circle" style="margin-bottom: 0;">{{ kiIcon("compass", 20) }}</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin: 0;">The Charter</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">An identity document that declares the island's name, its principal, its council, and its <strong>adoption table</strong> — which activities are enacted as-specified and which are vetoed or adapted.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Required fields: island name · principal · task prefix · council roster · adoption decisions</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-ki">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <div class="symbol-circle symbol-circle-forest" style="margin-bottom: 0;">{{ kiIcon("tree", 20) }}</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin: 0;">Knowledge Capital</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The island-specific realisation: council membership, citizenship records, routing configuration, integration settings, and the Calendar of activity. This is what makes a generic model concrete for your island.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Holds: council · citizenship · integrations · routing · calendar</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-ki">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <div class="symbol-circle symbol-circle-teal" style="margin-bottom: 0;">{{ kiIcon("harbour", 20) }}</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin: 0;">Contribution Process</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The governance mechanism for all changes to the canonical Library. Without a defined process, the Library drifts — entries accumulate without ratification, structure erodes. The process is what keeps the Library trustworthy.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Gate for: all Pillar changes · new conventions · activity adoption</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Territories & Archipelago -->
<section class="section-mist section-pad">
  <div class="page-container" style="max-width: 64rem;">
    <p class="overline">Federation</p>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.875rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Territories and Archipelagos</h2>
    <p class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">No island is an island forever. Knowledge Islands are designed to federate — to share conventions, propose changes to the canonical model, and form territories without surrendering independence.</p>

    <div class="grid-2col" style="gap: 2rem; align-items: start;">
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Territories</h3>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">A <strong>territory</strong> is one or more islands under shared jurisdiction. The key member is the <strong>principal island</strong> — the seat of governance, the one that holds the Knowledge Capital and the Charter for the whole territory. Any additional islands in the territory are <strong>satellites</strong>: they share governance conventions but maintain their own stores and may have distinct scope or audience.</p>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">The boundary rule is simple: if customs exist between two stores — if material doesn't flow freely without controls — they are separate territories. If everything flows freely, they are one island.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Archipelagos</h3>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">An <strong>archipelago</strong> is a geographic concept — a natural grouping of islands by proximity or shared character, independent of governance. A territory may contain one archipelago or span several; an archipelago may sit wholly within one territory or straddle two. Islands that share a common parent model can propose changes to that canonical model via the Contribution Process, but the change must be generic enough to benefit all islands, not just the proposing territory.</p>
        <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
          <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;"><strong>Arcadia in an archipelago:</strong> Arcadia is the canonical instance — the model's source of truth. An island adopting Arcadia's model references it; if they find a gap or a better approach, they can propose a change via the Contribution Process. The change is assessed by Arcadia's Council before any update to the canonical Library.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 2.5rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-ocean); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1.25rem;">
        <div style="flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--color-parchment); margin-top: 0.125rem;">{{ kiIcon("archipelago", 24) }}</div>
        <div>
          <p style="color: var(--color-parchment); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;"><strong style="color: white;">The boundary principle.</strong> Independent knowledge stores with shared governance are a <em>territory</em>. Islands in geographic proximity or sharing a natural character form an <em>archipelago</em>. These are orthogonal structures — a territory may span multiple archipelagos; an archipelago may bridge multiple territories. The governance question (whose Enactment Process ratifies a change?) is always answered by territory, not by geography.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

